nment |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/coronavirus-hits-spains-government/ |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=[[Euractiv]] |date=13 March 2020}}</ref> [[Carmen Leyte]], Spanish Senator of the conservative [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]] in representation of [[Province of Ourense|Ourense]] tests positive for COVID-19, becoming the first member of the Senate to be affected by the disease.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/4185925/0/la-senadora-del-pp-por-ourense-carmen-leyte-da-positivo-por-covid-19/|title=La senadora del PP por Ourense Carmen Leyte da positivo por Covid-19|last=20minutos|date=12 March 2020|website=20minutos.es - \u00daltimas Noticias|language=es|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Ministry of the Interior (Spain)|Ministry of the Interior]] decided to isolate its 69 jails.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elpais.com/espana/2020-03-12/interior-eleva-a-16-las-carceles-aisladas-para-evitar-la-expansion-del-coronavirus.html|title=Interior decide aislar sus 69 centros penitenciarios|last=L\u00f3pez-Fonseca|first=\u00d3scar|date=12 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|language=es|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Sagrada Familia]], in Barcelona, closed for tourists and construction workers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-spain-sagrada-fami/barcelonas-sagrada-familia-landmark-to-close-to-tourists-over-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z25D|title=Barcelona's Sagrada Familia landmark to close to tourists over coronavirus|last=Reuters|newspaper=Reuters|date=12 March 2020|language=en|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> The Catalan Government ordered a quarantine of the city of [[Igualada]] and the towns of [[Vilanova del Cam\u00ed]], [[\u00d2dena]] and [[Santa Margarida de Montbui]] after Igualada Hospital became a contagion focus. This first measure in Spain will affect 70,000 people during 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elpais.com/espana/catalunya/2020-03-12/ordenan-el-confinamiento-