]] (''The Famous Jett Jackson'') guest stars, along with the NFL's [[Warrick Dunn]].\n| LineColor       = A52A2A\n}}\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 59\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 19\n| Title           = Basketball Diaries\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = {{Start date|2003|5|31}}\n| OriginalAirDate = 204\n| ShortSummary    = Superstar athletes [[Grant Hill]] and [[Tony Dorsett]] appear as themselves in this episode, in which Coleman is hesitant to compete in a father-son basketball game. Meanwhile, Hilary gives Leo a glamorous makeover.\n| LineColor       = A52A2A\n}}\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 60\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n| Title           = Owning Up\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = {{Start date|2003|10|11}}\n| OriginalAirDate = 211\n| ShortSummary    = When Coleman's birdhouse is poorly done, he sneaks in to school and tries to claim somebody else's birdhouse as his. Morgan detects he's hiding something, so the jersey jumps Morgan and Coleman into the middle of nowhere during a head to head motocross race.\n| LineColor       = A52A2A\n}}\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 61\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 21\n| Title           = The New Kid in Town\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = {{Start date|2003|11|1}}\n| OriginalAirDate = 213\n| ShortSummary    = Larry is a sore loser after being defeated in a game of billiards by Hilary; Elliot enters the body of [[BMX]] rider [[Ryan Nyquist]].\n| LineColor       = A52A2A\n}}\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 62\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 22\n| Title           = Player Faker\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = {{Start date|2003|11|8}}\n| OriginalAirDate = 220\n| ShortSummary    = WNBA stars [[Cynthia Cooper-Dyke|Cynthia Cooper]] and [[Sheryl Swoopes]] find themselves involved in a hoops dispute between Morgan and Tamika.\n| LineColor       = A52A2A\n}}\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber  