{"title_page": "Lazarat", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement AL\n|type               = mu\n|official_name      = Lazarat\n|image_flag         = \n|image_shield       = \n|image_skyline      = File:Lazarat.jpg\n|image_caption      = Lazarat\n|image_location     = \n|county             = \n|municipality       = \n|leader_name        = Mr Green\n|leader_party       = \n|coordinates        = {{coord|40|3|N|20|9|E|type:adm1st_region:AL_dim:100000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|elevation_min      = \n|elevation_max      = \n|area_total         = \n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_unit   = 2801\n|postal_code        = 6004\n|area_code          = \n|car_plates         = GJ\n|website            = \n}}\n'''Lazarat''' ({{lang-sq-definite|Lazarati}}) is a village in [[Gjirokast\u00ebr County]], in southern [[Albania]]. It is located in the Dropull valley.<ref name= Konstantinos4647/> Formerly functioning as a [[municipality]], as part of the 2015 local government reform, it became a subdivision of the municipality of [[Gjirokast\u00ebr]].<ref>[http://www.reformaterritoriale.al/images/presentations/Ligji%20ndarja%20territoriale_Fletore_zyrtare.pdf Law nr. 115/2014] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924085559/http://www.reformaterritoriale.al/images/presentations/Ligji%20ndarja%20territoriale_Fletore_zyrtare.pdf |date=2015-09-24 }}</ref> The former municipality consisted of the villages Lazarat and [[Kordhoc\u00eb]].<ref>[http://www.interreg.gr/inst/interreg/gallery/File/Programmes/Greece%20-%20Albania/Simpliroma%20Programmatismou/EN/18-12-07_Programme_Complement_GREECE%20ALBANIA.doc Greece \u2013 Albania Neighbourhood Programme] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327014915/http://www.interreg.gr/inst/interreg/gallery/File/Programmes/Greece%20-%20Albania/Simpliroma%20Programmatismou/EN/18-12-07_Programme_Complement_GREECE%20ALBANIA.doc |date=March 27, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe population at the 2011 census was 2,801.<ref name=census11>[http://www.instat.gov.al/media/195823/6__gjirokaster.pdf 2011 census results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053713/http://www.instat.gov.al/media/195823/6__gjirokaster.pdf |date=2016-03-04 }}</ref>\n\nIn recent years, Lazarat had gained the reputation as the [[cannabis]] capital of the country due to its large scale growth of cannabis by the local population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2013/08/17/is_albania_europes_new_marijuana_capital_partner/|title=Is Albania Europe\u2019s new marijuana capital?|author=Besar Likmeta|publisher=|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref> However, in June 2014, the Albanian government cracked down and destroyed the local production and transit of the drug.\n\n==Geography==\nLazarat is a village just outside [[Gjirokast\u00ebr]], situated on mountain slope of [[Mali i Gjer\u00eb]].\n\n==History==\nDuring the Ottoman period, following the emigration of village inhabitants to [[Thrace]], Labs from the nearby [[Kurvelesh (region)|Kurvelesh]] region were placed in Lazarat by Kaplan Pasha.<ref name= Konstantinos4647/> Amidst the [[Islamization of Albania#Southern Albania|socio-political turbulence]] of the late eighteenth century in the area, Lazarat had bandits and it became a shelter for outlaws and criminals.<ref name= Konstantinos4647>{{cite journal |last1=Konstantinos. |first1=Giakoumis |title=The monasteries of Jorgucat and Vanishte in Dropull and of Spelaio in Lunxheri as monuments and institutions during the Ottoman period in Albania (16th-19th centuries) |date=2002 |page= 46-47|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Kosta_Giakoumis/publication/237149098_Giakoumis_K_2002_The_Monasteries_of_Jorgucat_and_Vanishte_in_Dropull_and_of_Spelaio_in_Lunxheri_as_Monuments_and_Institutions_During_the_Ottoman_Period_in_Albania_16th-19th_Centuries_Doctoral_thesis_s/links/5970774f4585158a480721a1/Giakoumis-K-2002-The-Monasteries-of-Jorgucat-and-Vanishte-in-Dropull-and-of-Spelaio-in-Lunxheri-as-Monuments-and-Institutions-During-the-Ottoman-Period-in-Albania-16th-19th-Centuries-Doctoral-thesis.pdf|accessdate=8 July 2018 }}</ref>\n\nSince the Albanian Government's attempts to stop the illegal cultivation of cannabis, there have been a growing number of activists from around the region demanding a special status for the small commune.  The activists demand the right to legalize production and selling of cannabis inside municipality borders. The Albanian government has rejected the demand.<ref>[http://www.carbonated.tv/news/albanian-village-europes-weed-capital Albanian Village Europe's Weed Capital], Carbonated TV</ref>\n\n==Crime==\nIn June 2014, [[Albanian police]] launched a major operation against the village, involving over 800 officers.<ref name=\"bbc\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/jun/17/albanian-cannabis-growers-800-police-battle-lazarat|title=Albanian cannabis growers and 800 police battle in lawless village of Lazarat|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref> Heavily armed locals shot [[Rocket-propelled grenade|RPGs]] and fired mortar rounds at the officers, who returned fire.<ref name=\"Guardian-crackdown\">{{cite web| title=Grenades fired at Albanian police during cannabis crackdown | website=[[The Guardian]] | date=16 June 2014 | url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/jun/16/albania-police-lazarat-cannabis-marijuana-crackdown | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> Police took control of most of the village, with Interior Minister [[Saimir Tahiri]] saying the operation would continue until \"every square centimetre in Lazarat is under state control\". Smoke rose from the village as locals reportedly burned cannabis plants.<ref name=\"bbc\"/>\n\nOn 24 June 2015, a member of the Albanian counter-terrorist force [[RENEA]] was shot and killed in the town, and two other soldiers wounded.<ref name=\"reutersrenea\">{{cite web | last=Koleka | first=Benet | title=Albanian policeman shot dead in former cannabis stronghold | website=[[Reuters]] | date=24 June 2015 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-albania-police-attacks-idUSKBN0P418R20150624 | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> A car containing gunmen had been stopped at a checkpoint, with attackers then opening fire on the soldiers from a nearby house.<ref name=\"reutersrenea\" /> Ibrahim Basha was a RENEA officer who had previously served with [[NATO]] in [[Afghanistan]]. The [[United States]] Ambassador to Albania, [[Donald Lu]], expressed condolences at the soldier's funeral, calling the incident a \"national tragedy\".<ref>http://tirana.usembassy.gov/news-events/ambassadors-remarks2/ambassador-lu-remarks-at-the-funeral-of-renea-officer-ibrahim-basha-june-25-2015.html</ref> Additional police and [[RENEA]] officers were sent to reinforce the town and locate the attackers.<ref name=\"reutersrenea\" /><ref>http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/albania-police-continue-massive-manhunt-for-cop-killer</ref>\n\n==Population==\nLazarat is inhabited by Muslim [[Albanians]],<ref name= Kallivretakis>Kallivretakis, Leonidas (1995). \"[http://helios-eie.ekt.gr/EIE/handle/10442/8696 \u0397 \u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03cc\u03c4\u03b7\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c5\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf \u03c0\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b5\u03c9\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b4\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 [The Greek Community of Albania in terms of historical geography and demography].\" In Nikolakopoulos, Ilias, Kouloubis Theodoros A. & Thanos M. Veremis (eds). ''\u039f \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 [The Greeks of Albania]''. University of Athens. p. 51. \"AM \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03bf\u03af \u039c\u03bf\u03c5\u03c3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bc\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9\" p.56. \"LAZARATI \u039b\u0391\u0396\u0391\u03a1\u0391\u03a4\u0389 2909 \u0391\u039c.</ref> many of whom have traditionally been [[Bektashi Order|Bektashi]].\n\n==Economy==\nThe main activity is [[agriculture]], especially [[animal husbandry]]. The area is known for its [[dairy products]].\n\n==Cannabis==\nThe village produced 900 tonnes of cannabis annually, worth \u20ac4.5bn, equivalent to around half of Albania's gross domestic product.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-27916026|title=Albanian police battle cannabis growers in Lazarat|work=BBC News|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Popular culture==\nThe eponymous film ''The Brave'' (2019) (previously ''Lazarat'') is centred on the conflict between locals and the police.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5524630/ |title=The Brave (2019) |website=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=2019-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Albania Villagers Fear Lazarat Movie Will Stereotype Them | website=Balkan Insight | date=12 September 2016 | url=https://balkaninsight.com/2016/09/12/lazarat-burning-movie-concerns-villagers-in-albania-09-10-2016/ | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=The Brave, il film che racconta la lotta contro la criminalit\u00e0 al villaggio di Lazarat, Albania | website=Albania News | date=5 October 2018 | url=https://www.albanianews.it/cultura/the-brave-film-criminalita-lazarat | language=it | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite news |title=Lazarat Burning - Hollywood film about Albanian Marijuana village |first=|last= |url=http://www.ocnal.com/2016/03/lazarat-burning-hollywood-film-about.html |newspaper=Oculus News |date=March 2016  |accessdate=}}\n\n{{Commons category|Lazarat}}\n{{Gjirokast\u00ebr div}}\n{{Gjirokast\u00ebr County new}}\n\n[[Category:Former municipalities in Gjirokast\u00ebr County]]\n[[Category:Administrative units of Gjirokast\u00ebr]]\n[[Category:Villages in Gjirokast\u00ebr County]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement AL\n|type               = mu\n|official_name      = Lazarat\n|image_flag         = \n|image_shield       = \n|image_skyline      = File:Lazarat.jpg\n|image_caption      = Lazarat\n|image_location     = \n|county             = \n|municipality       = \n|leader_name        = \n|leader_party       = \n|coordinates        = {{coord|40|3|N|20|9|E|type:adm1st_region:AL_dim:100000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|elevation_min      = \n|elevation_max      = \n|area_total         = \n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_unit   = 2801\n|postal_code        = 6004\n|area_code          = \n|car_plates         = GJ\n|website            = \n}}\n'''Lazarat''' ({{lang-sq-definite|Lazarati}}) is a village in [[Gjirokast\u00ebr County]], in southern [[Albania]]. It is located in the Dropull valley.<ref name= Konstantinos4647/> Formerly functioning as a [[municipality]], as part of the 2015 local government reform, it became a subdivision of the municipality of [[Gjirokast\u00ebr]].<ref>[http://www.reformaterritoriale.al/images/presentations/Ligji%20ndarja%20territoriale_Fletore_zyrtare.pdf Law nr. 115/2014] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924085559/http://www.reformaterritoriale.al/images/presentations/Ligji%20ndarja%20territoriale_Fletore_zyrtare.pdf |date=2015-09-24 }}</ref> The former municipality consisted of the villages Lazarat and [[Kordhoc\u00eb]].<ref>[http://www.interreg.gr/inst/interreg/gallery/File/Programmes/Greece%20-%20Albania/Simpliroma%20Programmatismou/EN/18-12-07_Programme_Complement_GREECE%20ALBANIA.doc Greece \u2013 Albania Neighbourhood Programme] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327014915/http://www.interreg.gr/inst/interreg/gallery/File/Programmes/Greece%20-%20Albania/Simpliroma%20Programmatismou/EN/18-12-07_Programme_Complement_GREECE%20ALBANIA.doc |date=March 27, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe population at the 2011 census was 2,801.<ref name=census11>[http://www.instat.gov.al/media/195823/6__gjirokaster.pdf 2011 census results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053713/http://www.instat.gov.al/media/195823/6__gjirokaster.pdf |date=2016-03-04 }}</ref>\n\nIn recent years, Lazarat had gained the reputation as the [[cannabis]] capital of the country due to its large scale growth of cannabis by the local population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2013/08/17/is_albania_europes_new_marijuana_capital_partner/|title=Is Albania Europe\u2019s new marijuana capital?|author=Besar Likmeta|publisher=|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref> However, in June 2014, the Albanian government cracked down and destroyed the local production and transit of the drug.\n\n==Geography==\nLazarat is a village just outside [[Gjirokast\u00ebr]], situated on mountain slope of [[Mali i Gjer\u00eb]].\n\n==History==\nDuring the Ottoman period, following the emigration of village inhabitants to [[Thrace]], Labs from the nearby [[Kurvelesh (region)|Kurvelesh]] region were placed in Lazarat by Kaplan Pasha.<ref name= Konstantinos4647/> Amidst the [[Islamization of Albania#Southern Albania|socio-political turbulence]] of the late eighteenth century in the area, Lazarat had bandits and it became a shelter for outlaws and criminals.<ref name= Konstantinos4647>{{cite journal |last1=Konstantinos. |first1=Giakoumis |title=The monasteries of Jorgucat and Vanishte in Dropull and of Spelaio in Lunxheri as monuments and institutions during the Ottoman period in Albania (16th-19th centuries) |date=2002 |page= 46-47|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Kosta_Giakoumis/publication/237149098_Giakoumis_K_2002_The_Monasteries_of_Jorgucat_and_Vanishte_in_Dropull_and_of_Spelaio_in_Lunxheri_as_Monuments_and_Institutions_During_the_Ottoman_Period_in_Albania_16th-19th_Centuries_Doctoral_thesis_s/links/5970774f4585158a480721a1/Giakoumis-K-2002-The-Monasteries-of-Jorgucat-and-Vanishte-in-Dropull-and-of-Spelaio-in-Lunxheri-as-Monuments-and-Institutions-During-the-Ottoman-Period-in-Albania-16th-19th-Centuries-Doctoral-thesis.pdf|accessdate=8 July 2018 }}</ref>\n\nSince the Albanian Government's attempts to stop the illegal cultivation of cannabis, there have been a growing number of activists from around the region demanding a special status for the small commune.  The activists demand the right to legalize production and selling of cannabis inside municipality borders. The Albanian government has rejected the demand.<ref>[http://www.carbonated.tv/news/albanian-village-europes-weed-capital Albanian Village Europe's Weed Capital], Carbonated TV</ref>\n\n==Crime==\nIn June 2014, [[Albanian police]] launched a major operation against the village, involving over 800 officers.<ref name=\"bbc\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/jun/17/albanian-cannabis-growers-800-police-battle-lazarat|title=Albanian cannabis growers and 800 police battle in lawless village of Lazarat|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref> Heavily armed locals shot [[Rocket-propelled grenade|RPGs]] and fired mortar rounds at the officers, who returned fire.<ref name=\"Guardian-crackdown\">{{cite web| title=Grenades fired at Albanian police during cannabis crackdown | website=[[The Guardian]] | date=16 June 2014 | url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/jun/16/albania-police-lazarat-cannabis-marijuana-crackdown | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> Police took control of most of the village, with Interior Minister [[Saimir Tahiri]] saying the operation would continue until \"every square centimetre in Lazarat is under state control\". Smoke rose from the village as locals reportedly burned cannabis plants.<ref name=\"bbc\"/>\n\nOn 24 June 2015, a member of the Albanian counter-terrorist force [[RENEA]] was shot and killed in the town, and two other soldiers wounded.<ref name=\"reutersrenea\">{{cite web | last=Koleka | first=Benet | title=Albanian policeman shot dead in former cannabis stronghold | website=[[Reuters]] | date=24 June 2015 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-albania-police-attacks-idUSKBN0P418R20150624 | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> A car containing gunmen had been stopped at a checkpoint, with attackers then opening fire on the soldiers from a nearby house.<ref name=\"reutersrenea\" /> Ibrahim Basha was a RENEA officer who had previously served with [[NATO]] in [[Afghanistan]]. The [[United States]] Ambassador to Albania, [[Donald Lu]], expressed condolences at the soldier's funeral, calling the incident a \"national tragedy\".<ref>http://tirana.usembassy.gov/news-events/ambassadors-remarks2/ambassador-lu-remarks-at-the-funeral-of-renea-officer-ibrahim-basha-june-25-2015.html</ref> Additional police and [[RENEA]] officers were sent to reinforce the town and locate the attackers.<ref name=\"reutersrenea\" /><ref>http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/albania-police-continue-massive-manhunt-for-cop-killer</ref>\n\n==Population==\nLazarat is inhabited by Muslim [[Albanians]],<ref name= Kallivretakis>Kallivretakis, Leonidas (1995). \"[http://helios-eie.ekt.gr/EIE/handle/10442/8696 \u0397 \u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03cc\u03c4\u03b7\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c5\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf \u03c0\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b5\u03c9\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b4\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 [The Greek Community of Albania in terms of historical geography and demography].\" In Nikolakopoulos, Ilias, Kouloubis Theodoros A. & Thanos M. Veremis (eds). ''\u039f \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 [The Greeks of Albania]''. University of Athens. p. 51. \"AM \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03bf\u03af \u039c\u03bf\u03c5\u03c3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bc\u03ac\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9\" p.56. \"LAZARATI \u039b\u0391\u0396\u0391\u03a1\u0391\u03a4\u0389 2909 \u0391\u039c.</ref> many of whom have traditionally been [[Bektashi Order|Bektashi]].\n\n==Economy==\nThe main activity is [[agriculture]], especially [[animal husbandry]]. The area is known for its [[dairy products]].\n\n==Cannabis==\nThe village produced 900 tonnes of cannabis annually, worth \u20ac4.5bn, equivalent to around half of Albania's gross domestic product.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-27916026|title=Albanian police battle cannabis growers in Lazarat|work=BBC News|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Popular culture==\nThe eponymous film ''The Brave'' (2019) (previously ''Lazarat'') is centred on the conflict between locals and the police.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5524630/ |title=The Brave (2019) |website=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=2019-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Albania Villagers Fear Lazarat Movie Will Stereotype Them | website=Balkan Insight | date=12 September 2016 | url=https://balkaninsight.com/2016/09/12/lazarat-burning-movie-concerns-villagers-in-albania-09-10-2016/ | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=The Brave, il film che racconta la lotta contro la criminalit\u00e0 al villaggio di Lazarat, Albania | website=Albania News | date=5 October 2018 | url=https://www.albanianews.it/cultura/the-brave-film-criminalita-lazarat | language=it | access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite news |title=Lazarat Burning - Hollywood film about Albanian Marijuana village |first=|last= |url=http://www.ocnal.com/2016/03/lazarat-burning-hollywood-film-about.html |newspaper=Oculus News |date=March 2016  |accessdate=}}\n\n{{Commons category|Lazarat}}\n{{Gjirokast\u00ebr div}}\n{{Gjirokast\u00ebr County new}}\n\n[[Category:Former municipalities in Gjirokast\u00ebr County]]\n[[Category:Administrative units of Gjirokast\u00ebr]]\n[[Category:Villages in Gjirokast\u00ebr County]]\n", "name_user": "188.3.153.67", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(This is true)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lazarat"}
{"title_page": "Shah Sulaim\u0101n N\u016bri", "text_new": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:Shah Sulem\u0101n N\u016bri}}\n{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 4.jpg|thumb|DARBAR SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN]]\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=drivesdk&usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|first=|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) Volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ziaetaiba.com/en/scholar/hazrat-sakhi-shah-suleman-noori|title=Hazrat Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori|website=www.ziaetaiba.com|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|url=http://archive.org/details/FAYZANENAUSHAHSecondEdition|title=FAYZAN-E NAUSHAH Second Edition}}</ref> also known as \"Sakhi Badshah\". He was a well known scholar,saint and Sufi of [[Qadiriyya]] silsila in sub-continent(Now Punjab,Pakistan).His Spirtual leader and \"Murshid\" was Syed Shah Maroof Khushabi.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|first=|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation)  volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook&usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> He spent his whole live in devotion and love for Allah.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" |SHAH SULEMAN\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |SAKHI BADSHAH,NOORI HAZOORI\n|-\n!Born\n|9TH RABI UL AWAL 1508\n|-\n!Residence\n|Purana Bhalwal Tehsil Bhalwal District Sargodha\n|-\n!Died\n|27TH RAMZAN UL MUBARIK FRIDAY NIGHT 1604\n|-\n!Major [[shrine]]\n|Purana Bhalwal Tehsil Bhalwal\n|-\n![[Calendar of saints|Feast]]\n|6th and 7th Muharram\n|-\n!Predecessor\n|SYED SHAH MAROOF\n|-\n!Successor\n|HAJI MUHAMMAD NAUSHA GANJ BAKSH\n|}\n\n= Birth & Parents =\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN father's name was Abdullah<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\"/><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|first=|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation)  volume 1 page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> who was also a kind and noble man and follower of Syed Shah Maroof Khushabi.His mother name was \"BIBI Bhaag Bhari\" she was also so generous and kind. Sakhi Shah Suleman was born on 9th Rabi ul Awal 1508.<ref name=\":0\" /> His Family lineage belongs to [[Quraysh]]<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n= EARLY LIFE & EDUCATION =\nHe got his early education from his parents. Shah Maroof used to visit Abdullah\"s house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 882|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> When Sakhi Shah Suleman was 4 years old he became the eye star of Shah Maroof.His Spirtual progress started in his childhood.\n\n= PERSONAL LIFE =\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN HAD TWO WIVES:\n\n# BIBI ROMAL KHATUN\n# BIBI JAURANA KHATUM<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 904|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n=== SONS ===\nHE HAD TWO SONS\n\n# RAHEEM DAAD\n# TAAJ MEHMOOD<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 905-6|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n= Family Lineage =\n\n===== KA'AB UL QARSHI\u2192MARAA\u2192QULAB\u2192QASSA\u2192ABDUL UL AZA\u2192 ASAD \u2192MUTLIB\u2192 ASAD\u2192 AMEER AYAZ\u2192 AMEER ABDUR REHMAN\u2192 AMEER ABDUR RAHEEM\u2192 MAROOF\u2192 ABDUL A'ALA\u2192 ABDUL UL SHAKOOR \u2192ADAM\u2192 MAZHAR \u2192ISMAEL\u2192 QASIM\u2192 AON\u2192 SULTAN ALI\u2192 KHUDA YAR\u2192 ABDUL KHALIQ\u2192 SHEIKH HUSSAIN \u2192MUHAMMAD SALEH\u2192 MUHAMMAD MURAD\u2192 SHAMS UDDIN\u2192 JALAL UDDIN \u2192ABDULLAH \u2192 SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI<ref name=\":0\" /> =====\n\n== SIMILARTIY ==\nTHE FAMILY LINEAGE OF [[Bahauddin Zakariya]] MULTANI AND SAKHI SHAH ARE SAME\n\nTHEIR FAMILY LINEAGE BECOME DIFFERENT FROM SONS OF ABDUR RAHEEM BIN ABDUR REHMAN\n\n= SPIRTUAL LINEAGE =\nHE GOT HIS SPIRTUAL TEACHINGS FROM SHAH MAROOF KHUSHABI\n\nHE BELONGED TO SILSILA E QARIYYA AS BELOW:\n\n* [[Muhammad]]\n* [[Ali]]\n* [[Hasan al-Basri]]\n* [[Habib al-Ajami]]\n* [[Dawud Tai]]\n* [[Maruf Karkhi]]\n* [[Sirri Saqti]]\n* [[Junayd of Baghdad]]\n* [[Abu Bakr Shibli]]\n* [[Abdul Aziz bin Hars bin Asad Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Abu Al Fazal Abdul Wahid Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Mohammad Yousuf Abu al-Farah Tartusi]]\n* [[Abul Hasan Hankari]]\n* [[Abu Saeed Mubarak Makhzoomi]]\n* [[Abdul Qadir Gilani]]\n* SYED ABDUL WAHAB GILANI\n* SYED ABDUL SALAM GILANI\n* SYED AHMAD GILANI\n* SYED MASOOD GILANI\n* SYED ALI GILANI\n* SYED SHAH MEER GILANI\n* SHAMS UDDIN GILANI\n* SHAH MUHAMAMD GHOAS GILANI\n* SYED MUBARIK HAQANI\n* SHAH MAROOF\n* SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n= TEACHINGS AND CHARACTERISTICS =\nWHEN SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI received THE \"KHILAFAT\",HE was ordered by his murshid to travel different places.So he travelled [[Shahpur]],[[Khushab]],[[Chawa]],Deowal,Jukali, TAKHT HAZAARA,KASHMIR AND GUJRAT.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 887|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Thousand of non Muslims became Muslims on his hands.After travel,his sheikh ordered him to reside in Purana Bhalwal (Now in tehsil Bhalwal,District Sargodha).Thousand of people from surrounding found straight way from them.\n\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN was strict follower of Shariat and Sunnat e Muhummad.He spent his mostly time in mosque in remembrance of Allah\n\nHe was so generous that he got the title of \"Sakhi\" .He was very kind to poors and needy ones.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 892|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n= SUCCESSORS =\nTHERE ARE MANY SUCCESSORS OF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI.SOME OF THEM ARE KNOWN AND SOME ARE UNKNOWN<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHIS KNOWN SUCCESSORS ARE FOLLOWING:\n\n[[Muhammad Qadiri]]: HE WAS SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN BELOVED SUCCESSORS WHICH FOUNDED THE NAUSHAYIA QADRIA SILSILA\n\nRAHEEM DAD : HE WAS THE ELDER SON OF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN\n\nTAJ MEHMOOD: HE WAS THE YOUNGER SON OF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN\n\nMULLAH KAREEM UDDIN JOKALVI\n\nDEWAN ABU AL FATAH KANBOHI\n\nMULLAH GHAZI GONDAL BHALWALI\n\nSHEIKH HAMMO FAQEER\n\nSHEIKH HINDI<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\"/>\n\n= SHRINE =\n[[File:HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 2.jpg|thumb|DARBAR SHARIF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI]]\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN SHRINE IS LOCATED IN PURANA BHALWAL,TEHSIL BHALWAL, DISTRICT SARGODHA<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.qadri-naushahi.com/Awliya/Genealogy2.html|title=Genealogy & Spiritual Lineage No. 25|last=|first=|date=|website=www.qadri-naushahi.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auqaf.punjab.gov.pk/shrines#sargodha|title=Shrines {{!}} Auqaf & Religious Affairs Department|website=auqaf.punjab.gov.pk|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Darbaar+Sakhi+Shah+Sulman+Noori+Hazoori/@32.2730345,72.8739842,17.83z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x3921a295ec3eff79:0x91434f6ac5759c18!8m2!3d32.2728078!4d72.8745575?shorturl=1|title=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|website=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n= DEATH =\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN DIED ON NIGHT OF FRIDAY 27TH RAMZAN UL MUBARIK 1604.HE DIED AT THE AGE 98 YEARS<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n[[Category:Sufism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Sufism]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n[[Category:Qadiri order]]\n__INDEX__\n__INDEX__\n[[Category:Sufism]]\n[[Category:Sufism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Qadiri order]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n__INDEX__\n__INDEX__\n__INDEX__\n", "text_old": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:Shah Sulem\u0101n N\u016bri}}\n{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 4.jpg|thumb|DARBAR SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN]]\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=drivesdk&usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|first=|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) Volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ziaetaiba.com/en/scholar/hazrat-sakhi-shah-suleman-noori|title=Hazrat Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori|website=www.ziaetaiba.com|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|url=http://archive.org/details/FAYZANENAUSHAHSecondEdition|title=FAYZAN-E NAUSHAH Second Edition}}</ref> also known as \"Sakhi Badshah\". He was a well known scholar,saint and Sufi of [[Qadiriyya]] silsila in sub-continent(Now Punjab,Pakistan).His Spirtual leader and \"Murshid\" was Syed Shah Maroof Khushabi.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|first=|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation)  volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook&usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> He spent his whole live in devotion and love for Allah.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" |SHAH SULEMAN\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |SAKHI BADSHAH,NOORI HAZOORI\n|-\n!Born\n|9TH RABI UL AWAL 1508\n|-\n!Residence\n|Purana Bhalwal Tehsil Bhalwal District Sargodha\n|-\n!Died\n|27TH RAMZAN UL MUBARIK FRIDAY NIGHT 1604\n|-\n!Major [[shrine]]\n|Purana Bhalwal Tehsil Bhalwal\n|-\n![[Calendar of saints|Feast]]\n|6th and 7th Muharram\n|-\n!Predecessor\n|SYED SHAH MAROOF\n|-\n!Successor\n|HAJI MUHAMMAD NAUSHA GANJ BAKSH\n|}\n\n= Birth & Parents =\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN father's name was Abdullah<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\"/><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|first=|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation)  volume 1 page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> who was also a kind and noble man and follower of Syed Shah Maroof Khushabi.His mother name was \"BIBI Bhaag Bhari\" she was also so generous and kind. Sakhi Shah Suleman was born on 9th Rabi ul Awal 1508.<ref name=\":0\" /> His Family lineage belongs to [[Quraysh]]<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n= EARLY LIFE & EDUCATION =\nHe got his early education from his parents. Shah Maroof used to visit Abdullah\"s house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 882|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> When Sakhi Shah Suleman was 4 years old he became the eye star of Shah Maroof.His Spirtual progress started in his childhood.\n\n= PERSONAL LIFE =\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN HAD TWO WIVES:\n\n# BIBI ROMAL KHATUN\n# BIBI JAURANA KHATUM<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 904|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n=== SONS ===\nHE HAD TWO SONS\n\n# RAHEEM DAAD\n# TAAJ MEHMOOD<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 905-6|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n= Family Lineage =\n\n===== KA'AB UL QARSHI\u2192MARAA\u2192QULAB\u2192QASSA\u2192ABDUL UL AZA\u2192 ASAD \u2192MUTLIB\u2192 ASAD\u2192 AMEER AYAZ\u2192 AMEER ABDUR REHMAN\u2192 AMEER ABDUR RAHEEM\u2192 MAROOF\u2192 ABDUL A'ALA\u2192 ABDUL UL SHAKOOR \u2192ADAM\u2192 MAZHAR \u2192ISMAEL\u2192 QASIM\u2192 AON\u2192 SULTAN ALI\u2192 KHUDA YAR\u2192 ABDUL KHALIQ\u2192 SHEIKH HUSSAIN \u2192MUHAMMAD SALEH\u2192 MUHAMMAD MURAD\u2192 SHAMS UDDIN\u2192 JALAL UDDIN \u2192ABDULLAH \u2192 SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI<ref name=\":0\" /> =====\n\n== SIMILARTIY ==\nTHE FAMILY LINEAGE OF [[Bahauddin Zakariya]] MULTANI AND SAKHI SHAH ARE SAME\n\nTHEIR FAMILY LINEAGE BECOME DIFFERENT FROM SONS OF ABDUR RAHEEM BIN ABDUR REHMAN\n\n= SPIRTUAL LINEAGE =\nHE GOT HIS SPIRTUAL TEACHINGS FROM SHAH MAROOF KHUSHABI\n\nHE BELONGED TO SILSILA E QARIYYA AS BELOW:\n\n* [[Muhammad]]\n* [[Ali]]\n* [[Hasan al-Basri]]\n* [[Habib al-Ajami]]\n* [[Dawud Tai]]\n* [[Maruf Karkhi]]\n* [[Sirri Saqti]]\n* [[Junayd of Baghdad]]\n* [[Abu Bakr Shibli]]\n* [[Abdul Aziz bin Hars bin Asad Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Abu Al Fazal Abdul Wahid Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Mohammad Yousuf Abu al-Farah Tartusi]]\n* [[Abul Hasan Hankari]]\n* [[Abu Saeed Mubarak Makhzoomi]]\n* [[Abdul Qadir Gilani]]\n* SYED ABDUL WAHAB GILANI\n* SYED ABDUL SALAM GILANI\n* SYED AHMAD GILANI\n* SYED MASOOD GILANI\n* SYED ALI GILANI\n* SYED SHAH MEER GILANI\n* SHAMS UDDIN GILANI\n* SHAH MUHAMAMD GHOAS GILANI\n* SYED MUBARIK HAQANI\n* SHAH MAROOF\n* SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n= TEACHINGS AND CHARACTERISTICS =\nWHEN SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI received THE \"KHILAFAT\",HE was ordered by his murshid to travel different places.So he travelled [[Shahpur]],[[Khushab]],[[Chawa]],Deowal,Jukali, TAKHT HAZAARA,KASHMIR AND GUJRAT.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 887|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Thousand of non Muslims became Muslims on his hands.After travel,his sheikh ordered him to reside in Purana Bhalwal (Now in tehsil Bhalwal,District Sargodha).Thousand of people from surrounding found straight way from them.\n\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN was strict follower of Shariat and Sunnat e Muhummad.He spent his mostly time in mosque in remembrance of Allah\n\nHe was so generous that he got the title of \"Sakhi\" .He was very kind to poors and needy ones.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 892|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n= SUCCESSORS =\nTHERE ARE MANY SUCCESSORS OF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI.SOME OF THEM ARE KNOWN AND SOME ARE UNKNOWN<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHIS KNOWN SUCCESSORS ARE FOLLOWING:\n\n[[Muhammad Qadiri]]: HE WAS SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN BELOVED SUCCESSORS WHICH FOUNDED THE NAUSHAYIA QADRIA SILSILA\n\nRAHEEM DAD : HE WAS THE ELDER SON OF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN\n\nTAJ MEHMOOD: HE WAS THE YOUNGER SON OF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN\n\nMULLAH KAREEM UDDIN JOKALVI\n\nDEWAN ABU AL FATAH KANBOHI\n\nMULLAH GHAZI GONDAL BHALWALI\n\nSHEIKH HAMMO FAQEER\n\nSHEIKH HINDI<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\"/>\n\n= SHRINE =\n[[File:HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 2.jpg|thumb|DARBAR SHARIF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI]]\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN SHRINE IS LOCATED IN PURANA BHALWAL,TEHSIL BHALWAL, DISTRICT SARGODHA<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1K2UBi_PY2EhAuVukqHmr89ZxpyN6IDau/view?usp=embed_facebook|title=\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912|last=|first=|date=|website=Google Docs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.qadri-naushahi.com/Awliya/Genealogy2.html|title=Genealogy & Spiritual Lineage No. 25|last=|first=|date=|website=www.qadri-naushahi.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auqaf.punjab.gov.pk/shrines#sargodha|title=Shrines {{!}} Auqaf & Religious Affairs Department|website=auqaf.punjab.gov.pk|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Darbaar+Sakhi+Shah+Sulman+Noori+Hazoori/@32.2730345,72.8739842,17.83z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x3921a295ec3eff79:0x91434f6ac5759c18!8m2!3d32.2728078!4d72.8745575?shorturl=1|title=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|website=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n= DEATH =\nSAKHI SHAH SULEMAN DIED ON NIGHT OF FRIDAY 27TH RAMZAN UL MUBARIK 1604.HE DIED AT THE AGE 98 YEARS<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n[[Category:Sufism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Sufism]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n[[Category:Qadiri order]]\n__INDEX__\n__INDEX__\n[[Category:Sufism]]\n[[Category:Sufism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Qadiri order]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n__INDEX__\n__INDEX__\n", "name_user": "Saadulhassan2", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shah_Sulaim%C4%81n_N%C5%ABri"}
