]] as Mother  \n* [[Victor Fairley]] as Grete's Father  \n* [[Richard Wydler]] as Grete's Brother  \n* [[Brenda Senton]] as Grete's Sister  \n* [[Wilfred Noy]] as Director of Opera Falkenheim  \n* [[Grete Natzler]] as Director of Opera's Daughter  \n* [[Joe Hayman]] as Impresario  \n* [[Bertha Belmore]] as Masculine Lady at TableTen\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Low, Rachael. ''Filmmaking in 1930s Britain''. George Allen & Unwin, 1985.\n* Wood, Linda. ''British Films, 1927-1939''. British Film Institute, 1986.\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0025186}}\n\n{{Carmine Gallone}}\n\n[[Category:1933 films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:1930s musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Carmine Gallone]]\n[[Category:British musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films shot at Elstree Studios]]\n[[Category:British black-and-white films]]\n\n\n{{1930s-UK-film-stub}}\n{{musical-comedy-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Beryl reid fan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Going_Gay"}
